
🚀 Day 69 of hashtag#100DaysOfCode Challenge – Monitoring Tools (Part 2)
As I continue my journey in cybersecurity, today I explored SIEM (Security Information and Event Management) and Network Monitoring Tools! 🛡️

🔍 Key Takeaways:
 ✅ OSSIM (Open Source SIEM) – A powerful tool for security monitoring, log management, and incident response.
 ✅ AlienVault SIEM – Integrates multiple security tools for threat detection, behavioral monitoring, and compliance auditing.
 ✅ AirServer – A screen monitoring tool that works across Windows, macOS, iOS, Android, and Chromebook devices.
 ✅ Acrylic Wi-Fi Analyzer – A wireless network monitoring tool with features like Wi-Fi scanning, signal strength analysis, packet capture, and security auditing.
💡 Use Cases:
 🔹 Enterprise-level threat monitoring
 🔹 Incident response & forensic analysis
 🔹 Penetration testing & security auditing
Cybersecurity is all about staying ahead of threats, and mastering these tools is a crucial step toward that goal! 🔥
What monitoring tools do you use in your security workflow? Let’s discuss! 👇
